---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../components/ui/Container.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for blkpixel.com, in line with the GDPR and the Austrian Datenschutzgesetz (DSG)."
>
  <Container class="py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-[var(--muted)]">
      Datenschutzerklärung — how this site handles data, in line with the GDPR and the Austrian
      Datenschutzgesetz (DSG).
    </p>

    <article class="prose prose-neutral mt-10 max-w-none dark:prose-invert">
      <h2>Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        blkPixel FlexCo, represented by Oliver Tulla. Contact:{' '}
        <a href="mailto:oliver@blkpixel.com">oliver@blkpixel.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What This Site Collects</h2>
      <p>
        This site is static — there's no contact form, no account system, and no analytics or
        tracking scripts installed. The only thing stored client-side is a dark/light theme
        preference, saved via your browser's <code>localStorage</code>. It never leaves your
        browser and isn't linked to you personally.
      </p>
      <p>
        Like any web server, whichever hosting provider serves this site will process standard
        technical connection data (e.g. IP address, request timestamp, user agent) in its access
        logs, purely to deliver the page and keep the service secure. This is unavoidable for any
        website and is processed under legitimate interest (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR), not for tracking
        or profiling.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This site does not set cookies. The theme preference above uses{' '}
        <code>localStorage</code>, not a cookie, and nothing is transmitted to a server.
      </p>

      <h2>Third Parties</h2>
      <p>
        Project pages link out to third-party services (e.g. GitHub, GitHub Pages, Firebase-hosted
        demos, EasyEDA/OSHWLab, Onshape). Once you follow one of those links, that service's own
        privacy policy applies — this policy only covers blkpixel.com itself.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR you have the right to access, rectify, or erase any personal data
        concerning you, to restrict or object to its processing, and to data portability. Since
        this site doesn't currently collect any personal data of its own, there's nothing on file
        to request — but reach out to{' '}
        <a href="mailto:oliver@blkpixel.com">oliver@blkpixel.com</a> with any questions. You also
        have the right to lodge a complaint with the Austrian data protection authority
        (Datenschutzbehörde).
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        This policy will be updated if the site adds anything that processes personal data — a
        contact form or analytics, for example.
      </p>
    </article>
  </Container>
</BaseLayout>
